<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-13T13:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-13T13:36:00-05:00" n="1229" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1229">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.63/362</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Parker</persName>,
                                representing American interests, to the <gloss type="to">Secretary
                                    of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-13T12:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 13, 1917, 12
                                noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>675. Department’s 661, February 12, 4 p.m. Minister Fomento Morry
                            informed me that he had taken up with General Carranza the matter of
                            declaring forfeited the properties of such persons as have not complied
                            with decree or asked for extension. He pointed out that five months have
                            elapsed since the issuance of the decree and that he considered that
                            this was sufficient time for interested parties to have shown cause for
                            nonoperation. I do not think decree will be withdrawn but my impression
                            is that no drastic action will be taken although I have nothing official
                            on which to base my opinion. Have again taken matter up with Foreign
                            Office.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Parker</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>